{"metadata":{"title":"Defining Routes","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"SwiftRouting"}],"role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Routes are the foundation of SwiftRouting. They define all possible navigation destinations in your app as type-safe Swift enums."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Creating-a-Route-Enum","text":"Creating a Route Enum"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A route is any enum that conforms to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftRouting\/documentation\/SwiftRouting\/Route","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. Each case represents a distinct screen or destination."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["enum HomeRoute: Route {","    case home","    case profile(userId: String)","    case settings","    case detail(item: Item)","    ","    var name: String {","        switch self {","        case .home: \"home\"","        case .profile(let userId): \"profile(\\(userId))\"","        case .settings: \"settings\"","        case .detail(let item): \"detail(\\(item.id))\"","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"The-name-Property","text":"The name Property"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"name","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property provides a human-readable identifier used for:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Logging and debugging","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Router identification"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Analytics tracking","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Include relevant associated values in the name to make logs more informative."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Mapping-Routes-to-Views","text":"Mapping Routes to Views"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Conform your route to ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftRouting\/documentation\/SwiftRouting\/RouteDestination","isActive":true},{"text":" to define which view each route displays:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["extension HomeRoute: RouteDestination {","    static func view(for route: HomeRoute) -> some View {","        switch route {","        case .home:","            HomeView()","        case .profile(let userId):","            ProfileView(userId: userId)","        case .settings:","            SettingsView()","        case .detail(let item):","            DetailView(item: item)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Nested Routes and Nested Destinations","anchor":"Nested-Routes-and-Nested-Destinations","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For larger apps, you can model feature subflows as nested routes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Keep the top-level route as the destination entry point, and render child routes through dedicated destination views.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["enum AppRoute: Route {","    case home","    case profile(ProfileRoute)","","    var name: String {","        switch self {","        case .home:","            \"home\"","        case .profile(let child):","            \"profile.\\(child.name)\"","        }","    }","}","","enum ProfileRoute: Route {","    case overview","    case edit(userId: String)","","    var name: String {","        switch self {","        case .overview:","            \"overview\"","        case .edit(let userId):","            \"edit(\\(userId))\"","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Map from the top-level destination:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["extension AppRoute: RouteDestination {","    static func view(for route: AppRoute) -> some View {","        switch route {","        case .home:","            HomeView()","        case .profile(let child):","            ProfileRouteDestination(route: child)","        }","    }","}","","struct ProfileRouteDestination: View {","    let route: ProfileRoute","","    var body: some View {","        switch route {","        case .overview:","            ProfileOverviewView()","        case .edit(let userId):","            ProfileEditView(userId: userId)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Only the route type used by ","type":"text"},{"code":"RoutingView(destination:root:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (for example ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppRoute","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") needs to conform to ","type":"text"},{"code":"RouteDestination","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Child route enums (for example ","type":"text"},{"code":"ProfileRoute","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") can remain plain ","type":"text"},{"code":"Route","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" types.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"text":"Customizing Routing Type","anchor":"Customizing-Routing-Type","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, routes use push navigation. Override "},{"code":"routingType","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to change this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["enum HomeRoute: Route {","    case home","    case settings","    case fullScreenModal","    ","    var name: String { \/* ... *\/ }","    ","    var routingType: RoutingType {","        switch self {","        case .fullScreenModal:","            return .cover","        case .settings:","            return .sheet()","        default:","            return .push","        }","    }